parameters: I was born here, I'll die here!
\af[1]\n<\N[1]>Sir, we're going to need stubborn people like you on AGM Station.
\af[1]\n<\N[1]>You owe it to society to go there.
You're right. I do! See you there. I'll make you a better person.
\af[2]\n<\N[2]>Then why are you just sitting here?
There’s no point in trying anymore.
\af[1]\n<\N[1]>You can be old and tired on Mars!
\af[2]\n<\N[2]>I’m too moved to be confused by your choice of words.
I’m not… What do you mean, girl?
\af[1]\n<\N[1]>I mean that you shouldn’t give up now. Give up in space.
You remind me of my grandchildren.
Oh honey, we need to go.
He’s a scruffy boy with brown hair.
\af[1]\n<\N[1]>Come with me, we can look out for him.
\n<\N[2]>Now can we please take care of ourselves?
Thank goodness! I can finally get out of here!
You stopped to talk to me?
I didn't think anyone would care.
\af[1]\n<\N[1]>I care. Get to the station, and I'm sure you'll meet more people who care.
\af[1]\n<\N[1]>Then we'll definitely have to meet again.
I'm scared, I want my mommy!
She wears a dress and a kerchief over her hair.
Please help me find my son!
Please help me find my son!
